SUMMARY:Renegade Orchestra at Hall of the Above
DESCRIPTION:The Renegade Orchestra is the bay area’s most rock and roll symphony. Is it a rock band? Is it an orchestra? Who knows? But it’s definitely the best of both worlds. The pure unbridled fury of some of the bay area’s top orchestra players unleashed on classic rock songs backed up by a hard-hitting rhythm section. \nFor their show at the Hall of the Above in Petaluma on April 11\, the Renegade Orchestra will present a revolving set of music all based on the sounds of San Francisco…and the Bay Area\, featuring pieces written by famous Bay Area rock bands or even just recorded in the Bay Area. These are classic tunes reimagined like Jefferson Airplane’s Somebody to Love\, It’s a Beautiful Day’s White Bird\, and even some orchestral punk by the Dead Kennedys. \nAt this show\, the Renegade Orchestra will present a comfortable\, but lively show featuring around 15 musicians\, all committed to having a relaxed and rocking time. If there is something you hate about orchestra concerts\, this is the opposite.
URL:https://golocal.coop/event/renegade-orchestra-at-hall-of-the-above/
LOCATION:Hall of the Above\, 199 Petaluma Blvd N.\, Petaluma\, CA
CATEGORIES:Music
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://golocal.coop/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Renegade-orchestra-s.jpg
GEO:38.235604;-122.641187
X-APPLE-STRUCTURED-LOCATION;VALUE=URI;X-ADDRESS=Hall of the Above 199 Petaluma Blvd N. Petaluma CA;X-APPLE-RADIUS=500;X-TITLE=199 Petaluma Blvd N.:geo:-122.641187,38.235604
END:VEVENT
