SUMMARY:Half-Mile High feat. Adam Spry & Ryan Woodard at the Penngrove Pub
DESCRIPTION:Half-Mile High creates songs that transport the listener to the raw\, unspoiled terrain of this hidden world. \n  \nHALF MILE HIGH BAND BIO \nHalf-Mile High’s Mercuryville years (2010-2018) coalesced with the tight-knit quartet of Shaun Bond\, Chris Bradley\, Preston Booker\, and Marc Hagenlocher. The Mercuryville Sessions EP is an artifact of that era\, which was a high-wire time of dizzying live appearances around the Bay Area and a fruitful era of expansive songwriting\, brotherhood\, and collaboration. The five songs compiled on The Mercuryville Sessions are much of all that remains of the recorded material from those years. The rest is memory and legend. \n  \nRYAN WOODARD BIO \nMeet Ryan Woodard\, a talented singer/songwriter and multifaceted musician from Sonoma County\, California. Born into a musical family on both sides\, Ryan’s innate talent was nurtured from an early age. Diagnosed with autism at three\, music became his solace and sanctuary. Despite being considered nonverbal until nine\, Ryan found comfort in the rhythms and lyrics that would eventually unlock his voice. He would listen to songs on loop until the words made sense\, sparking a lifelong passion.
URL:https://golocal.coop/event/half-mile-high-feat-adam-spry-ryan-woodard-at-the-penngrove-pub/
LOCATION:Penngrove Pub\, 10005 Main Street\, Penngrove\, CA
CATEGORIES:Music
GEO:38.297140;-122.666400
X-APPLE-STRUCTURED-LOCATION;VALUE=URI;X-ADDRESS=Penngrove Pub 10005 Main Street Penngrove CA;X-APPLE-RADIUS=500;X-TITLE=10005 Main Street:geo:-122.666400,38.297140
END:VEVENT
