SUMMARY:Boating at the Barn on the Petaluma River
DESCRIPTION:Explore the Petaluma River by boat through Friends’ FREE Boating at the Barn program. Use our fleet of kayaks\, canoes and stand-up-paddleboards to have your own River adventure and see the Petaluma River as you never have before. \nWe have life jackets from toddlers to adults\, and want to help you and your family experience the Petaluma River for yourself. This is an all-volunteer run program and we are always looking for new people to join our team on Sundays. Use the link below to sign up for an upcoming Sunday. \nHours: Sundays\, 10am – 1pm \nLocation: David Yearsley River Heritage Center (red barn)\, Steamer Landing Park\, 6 Copeland Street \nFREE \nDonations Welcome! Volunteers Needed!
URL:https://golocal.coop/event/boating-at-the-barn-on-the-petaluma-river-11/
LOCATION:David Yearsley River Heritage Center\, 6 Copeland St.\, Petaluma\, CA
CATEGORIES:Recreation
