SUMMARY:Juke Joint Jukebox
DESCRIPTION:Juke Joint Jukebox is an electrifying educational cabaret that brings the legends to life — Ella Fitzgerald\, Ray Charles\, Dorothy Dandridge\, Harry Belafonte\, and more. Part concert\, part history lesson\, this high-octane journey celebrates the artists who shaped American music with powerhouse vocals\, storytelling\, and irresistible rhythm. \nJuke Joint Jukebox features the vocal talents of Gary Stanford Jr.\, Bradley Kynard\, Skylaer Palacios\, Sharon Griffith\, Solona Husband and Leo Kimuyu. They are joined by pianist Victor Hall\, guitarist Greg Call\, and drummer Lance Lee. \nFilled with soaring songs\, poignant storytelling and live music\, Juke Joint Jukebox is a special event not to be missed! \nTickets available now at www.spreckelsonline.com or call the box office at 707-588-3400. \nJuke Joint Jukebox: A Historical Cabaret\nApril 10th – April 12th\nFriday at 7:30pm\, Saturday and Sunday at 2:00pm\nTickets: https://app.arts-people.com/index.php?show=316486
URL:https://golocal.coop/event/juke-joint-jukebox-3/
LOCATION:Spreckels Performing Arts Center\, 5409 Snyder Lane\, Rohnert Park\, 94928
CATEGORIES:Music,Theater
